Description: Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. Replicates the viral genomic DNA. This polymerase possesses two enzymatic activities: DNA synthesis (polymerase) and an exonucleolytic activity that degrades single-stranded DNA in the 3'-5' direction for proofreading purpose. The DNA synthesis very likely occurs by strand displacement. From Escherichia phage T5 (Enterobacteria phage T5).
β-lactamase; bla; confers resistance to ampicillin, carbenicillin, and related antibiotics
transcription terminator for bacteriophage T7 RNA polymerase
bidirectional E. coli tonB-P14 transcription terminator
LacZα fragment of β-galactosidase; lacZ fragment
